3.00	Olympic_Swimming_Pool	Olympic-size swimming pool	An Olympic-size swimming pool is the type of swimming pool used in the Olympic Games, where the race course is 50 meters in length. This is typically referred to as "long course", delineating it from "short course" which applies to competitions in pools that are either 25 meters or 25 yards in length.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Olympic_Swimming_Pool_-_Fast_Lane.JPG/220px-Olympic_Swimming_Pool_-_Fast_Lane.JPG
